cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on improving machine reading using recurrent neural networks and external knowledge bases. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves attention mechanisms, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves the use of continuous representations of knowledge bases, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
